For my Environmental Science 40 critical thinking course taken at UCSB, I chose to do a research essay on the effects of lithium mining. One of the main goals for this project was to be able to use and demonstrate critical thinking skills. Throughout the 10 week course I was able to learn different kinds of evidence, methods, and arguments to produce a research essay.

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="research_essay.pdf"&gt;Download PDF&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

The process for this project started with making a proposal on what my project is going to look like and how I plan on presenting it. This took me a week to complete. The second part of this process was to start doing research. I spent 2 weeks gathering and synthesizing information on the topic in order to move forward with essay. Th last step of this process was to start writing the essay, and make sure to utilize the critical thinking skills I learned through out the quarter.

